column2: Nuveen Municipal 2021 Target Term Fund (the Fund) is a diversified, closed-end management investment company. The Fund seeks to provide a high level of current income exempt from federal income tax and to return the original $9.85 net asset value (NAV) per common share on or about March 1, 2021. The Fund invests in a portfolio primarily of municipal securities, the income from which is exempt from regular federal income tax of the United States. At least 65% of its managed assets are invested in low- to medium-quality municipal securities that, at the time of investment, are rated BBB/Baa or lower or unrated but judged by the managers to be of comparable quality. The Fund's investment advisor and fund manager is Nuveen Fund Advisors, LLC.
